<BaseLayout title="Editorial policy and methodology" description="How Produto com IA selects sources, verifies information, uses artificial intelligence and publishes corrections." lang="en" alternateUrl="/politica-editorial/">
<article class="container article-body" style="padding-top:4rem;padding-bottom:4rem"><h1>Editorial policy and methodology</h1><p><strong>Last reviewed:</strong> July 22, 2026.</p><h2>Mission</h2><p>Produto com IA publishes practical artificial-intelligence analysis for product professionals. We separate signal from promotion, explain implications and connect material claims to sources.</p><h2>Sources and verification</h2><p>We prioritize official documentation, research papers, regulatory records and direct statements. Secondary sources provide context. Material figures, dates and quotations are checked before publication.</p><h2>Use of artificial intelligence</h2><p>AI tools may assist research, translation, organization and review. Rodrigo Tozato selects topics, verifies claims, edits and remains accountable for published content. Automated text is not presented as independent reporting.</p><h2>Conflicts and advertising</h2><p>Advertising does not determine editorial conclusions. Commercial relationships, sponsorships and compensated links will be disclosed on the relevant page.</p><h2>Updates and corrections</h2><p>Guides show publication and modification dates. Material errors are corrected and recorded on the <a href="/en/corrections/">corrections page</a>. Contact: <a href="mailto:rodrigo.tozato@icloud.com">rodrigo.tozato@icloud.com</a>.</p></article>
</BaseLayout>
